to the lobe of the ear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the two shoulder-joints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more than that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"what does not extend beyond the ears being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wfrp","text_ar":"وفرة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collective mass"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujotamaEa","text_ar":"مُجْتَمَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the hair of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyap","text_ar":"نَاصِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anterior part of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what reaches to the two shoulder-joints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) in the M it is said to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner in the Deewán el-Adab: but ISd adds that it is also said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair more in quantity than that which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lim~ap","text_ar":"لِمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to IAth, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair of the head that falls upon the two shoulder-joints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Muhedhdhib,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what extends beyond the ears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Mukaddameh of Z,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what extends to the lobe of the ear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to IDrd,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lim~apN","text_ar":"لِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waforapN","text_ar":"وَفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumamN","text_ar":"جُمَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAmN","text_ar":"جِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) dim. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumayomapN","text_ar":"جُمَيْمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY lumoEapF fagasalahaA bijum~atihi","text_ar":"رَاَى لُمْعَةً فَغَسَلَهَا بِجُمَّتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saw a spot, and washed it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a moistening of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jm~p","text_ar":"جمّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the water of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jm~p","text_ar":"جمّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": the prefixed noun being suppressed. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-  Also [app. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flower-bud;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbp","text_ar":"قبة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[rendered by Golius “ nodosior pars ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a plant, from which the flower comes forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) [See an ex. above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~a","text_ar":"جَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". If from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~apN","text_ar":"جُمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to hair, it would seem rather to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tuft."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha*afa jum~apu Aljawozapi vum~a A^akalahaA","text_ar":"حَذَفَ جُمَّةُ الجَوْزَةِ ثُمَّ اَكَلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw away the husk of the walnut: then ate it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","TA","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}